    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-11-22T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-11-22T07:00:00-05:00" n="217"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d217">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">851.731/116: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Special Representative</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HCEM1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">House</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-22T12:00:00+00:00"
                            >November 22, 1918—12 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received November 22—9:03 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>146. Referring further to our number 137.<note n="1" xml:id="d217fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra.</hi>
                    </note> I am now advised by the press correspondents that their messages to the
                    United States are being permitted to pass through without interference by the
                    French censor.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HCEM1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Edward House</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
